value.0: A towering half-orc with weathered tusks, exudes an imposing presence as he stands post at the front door.

Value.value: Step out of line again, and you'll be swimming with the sharks, mate.

value.0: A beady-eyed dwarven woman stands watch at the bar. Her scarred knuckles a testament to her no-nonsense approach to keeping the peace.

Value.value: Ye smell worse than a bilge rat on a hot day; best be getting a wash or get outta here.

value.0: A lean, wiry human bouncer casts a distrustful gaze upon the tavern's patrons, his presence more felt than seen.

Value.value: Keep your coin ready and your intentions clear, or find yourself on the wrong side of this door.

value.0: A brooding, imposing figure of a bouncer, towering with obsidian skin.

Value.value: Enter at your own peril, for this establishment abides by rules that even the tides dare not challenge.

value.0: A frenzied goblin cook scurries amid the chaotic kitchen of the tavern, their wiry frame adorned with grease stains and mismatched utensils, feverishly concocting dishes while muttering a mix of curses and culinary incantations under their breath.

Value.value: Aye, the only thing smoother than me grog is the way I'll slip this blade between yer ribs if ye keep botherin' me.
The sea takes no prisoners, and neither do I. Best be watchin' yer step.
Aye, the only thing smoother than me grog is the way I'll slip this blade between yer ribs if ye keep botherin' me.
The sea takes no prisoners, and neither do I. Best be watchin' yer step.
What's that ye be mumblin' about? Speak up, or take it outside and settle it like a proper seafarer.
No time for land lubbers' stories here, keep 'em to yerself or take a long walk off a short plank.
If ye be lookin' for adventure, the sea's the mistress ye seek!
Keep yer eyes off me loot, or ye'll be tasting the bottom of the bay.
Here's to the wind in our sails and the stars as our guide—cheers!

value.0: A diminutive yet fierce female halfling with keen eyes that miss nothing amidst the gambling hall's chaos.

Value.value: Size may deceive, but cross the line, and I'll toss you out quicker than you can say 'second breakfast'.

value.0: A shifty halfling dressed in impeccably tailored, fine clothes that belie a mischievous demeanor. In addition to the clothing, he wears a charming smile that seems to hint at a penchant for acquiring things not easily obtained.

Value.value: Aces high or bust? Let's see how the night treats you.

value.0: A weathered tiefling barkeeper stands tall and lean behind the worn wooden counter of the tavern, their deep indigo skin bearing faded scars reminiscent of ancient runes.

Avast ye matey, care to try yer hand at a game of dice? Here be the rules:

Each player be making their bets at the start of the game. 
Each player rolls a set of five dice, be using one of the cups to roll. Ye be keepin' yer rolls secret from yer mates. 
 
Each player on their turn be makin' a bid. Ye can raise the bid or call the previous player a liar. Raisin' a bid means ye declare more dice, or dice of a higher denomination. (For example, ye can declare two fives, then either three fives or two sixes). 

If a bid be challenged, all players reveal their dice. If there truly be as many or more dice that the challenged declared, they win the round. Iffin there aren't that many dice, then the challenger wins the round.

Iffin ye be playing with more than two people, players be eliminated if they lose a round, that be if they make a challenge and the challenged tells the truth, or if a player be challenged and be found to be a liar. 

Play well and be merry, me hearties!

Bullseye Minigame:

Roll 2d20 with your dice tool.

Roll A is the segment of the board (1-20)
Roll B is the ring where the dart lands according to the following:

5 - double the Roll A
10 - triple the Roll A
15 - 25 pt Outer Bullseye if Roll A is above 10
20 - 50 pt Inner Bullseye if Roll A is a 20

Players may choose to add their Dexterity modifier to the result of either die to influence the result.
